<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-924-634  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 924 634.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Lotus  Dec 1989 v5 n12 p17(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Lotus Publishing Corp. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>There's a scanner in your future. (Ideas andamp; Trends)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Friedman, Rich.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   BIS CAP International (reports).andO;Topic:     ScanningForecastingMarket AnalysisDesktop Publishing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>THERE'S A SCANNER IN YOUR FUTUREandM;In the next few years, desktop scanners will begin to compete for desk spacewith personal computers, printers, software manuals, and disk bins.andP;  Analystsat BIS CAP International, a market research firm in Norwell, Mass., predict a36% annual increase in scanner sales over the next four years, from 186,000units in 1988 to 876,000 in 1993.andM;Scanners, they say, are riding the crest of the desktop-publishing wave.andP;  Aspeople get accustomed to so-called compound documents--documents that containboth text and graphics--scanners will be essential for getting images intoyour computer.andM;As more people buy scanners, prices will drop.andP;  According to Ajit Kapoor, BISCAP's director of electronic imaging services, this year's $2,000 desktopscanner will cost $1,000 in 1993.andP;  Even as prices drop, scanners are gettingmore accurate and more versatile.andP;  Today you can buy a portable scanner, ascanner that can read colors, or a scanner large enough to handle hugeengineering drawings.andP;  Big-name companies, such as IBM, Hewlett-Packard,Xerox, Imaging Systems, and Apple, are all selling scanners.andM;Some industry observers, however, see problems ahead.andP;  The scanner market isstill too small to have a standardized software interface.andP;  Down the road,this may cause compatibility problems.andP;  And while many desktop computers nowhave the speed and memory capacity to store and manipulate images, images arestill major memory hogs.andP;  BIS CAP's Kapoor says that a single8-1/2-by-11-inch image scanned at 300 dots per inch with 64 gray levelsrequires an astounding 6 megabytes.andO;</TEXT></DOC>